Key Match Events: James Harden had 24 points and 12 rebounds for a double-double.
Norm Powell had 24 points against his former team, leading the Los Angeles Clippers past the Toronto Raptors 105-103.
Immanuel Quickley had 21 points and four assists in 25 minutes in his first game back from a bruised pelvis.
Quickley had a game-tying drive and game-tying three in the final 1:39.
RJ Barrett and Immanuel Quickley each missed lay-up attempts in the final seconds that could have extended the game.
Post-Match Reflections: Norm Powell expressed excitement and gratitude for the opportunity to be a go-to player.
Immanuel Quickley reflected on the joy of competing and the disappointment of not securing the win.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The game was held at the Intuit Dome, the most expensive arena ever built at a reported $2 billion.
The Clippers rank 27th in NBA attendance, averaging 16,643 fans per night in an arena built to hold 18,000.
The Clippers managed a sell-out on Saturday night despite their struggles.
